-- Bank of Beirut First-Half Net Income Rises 65% as Lending Increases
-- Massoud A. Derhally
-- 2010-07-23T13:22:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/bank-of-beirut-first-half-net-income-rises-65-as-lending-increases.html

          
          
             Bank of Beirut SAL , a publicly
traded Lebanese lender, said first-half profit rose 65 percent
to about 72.4 billion Lebanese pounds ($48 million) from 43.8
billion pounds a year earlier, as loans increased.  
 Lending grew 37 percent to 3 trillion pounds in the first
six months of the year from 2.1 trillion pounds, the bank said
today in a filing, according to an e-mailed statement from the
Beirut Stock Exchange.  
 Total assets grew 14.6 percent to 10.7 trillion pounds.  
